channel.title: [PROJECT]My dream server
channel.description:
Iv always wanted to have my dream server come true...every npc I could mapp..mapped using a command
what this project is:
[b]I am (with a little help from silabsoft and some other people) going to map every possible npc I can map tell me eyes drop out!! I am going to use arayn to find coords of npcs ID's of npcs and more! I am going to use RUNEHQ and tip.it to find npc drops and HP levels! Once this is done I will test it to see if everything works. Then I will start codding codes for talking npcs and adding the shops! Now I have done alot of things like mapping by myself so if I say "no" to a help question thats about mapping please Understand I can do it my self and am not trying to let you down![/b]
[glow=red,2,300]If someone could get/make me a working npc map command for whitescape like ::map Id rangeY1 rangeX1 range Y2 rangeX2 HP[/glow] like ::asp in Scaperune...I WILL BE SO DAM HAPPY! I HAVE ALWAYS WANTED TO MAP NPCS USING COMMANDS!!!! I WILL GIVE YOU MY 2MB FULL OF SOURCE CODES AND ALL THE RS2 CASH POSSIBLE FOR MAKING MY DREAM COME TRUE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
so yeah Survival scape wont be on for awhile...the people I will need help with ill pm you guys k? (you dont know who you are :) )
so yeah lol wish me luck!! I wont be on msn for awhile lol
[glow=red,2,300]===============STATUS PAGE===============[/glow] Lumby npcs: 89% Finished mapping them now I gatta fix some talking features and glitches :P
All new items: 95%! still gatta add a little more items...
Camelot Npcs: 50% done. added Sir jerro and Sir harry. Might at 2 more camelot guys then ill be done.
Catherby npcs: 19% done. Added fisherman and fish store. Gatta add a little more stuff to fish store and bankers ect..

item.title: [PROJECT]My dream server
item.dc:creator: @Fasga Fasga
item.description:
@Fasga wrote:

Ok, here goes.

	if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("map"))
	{
		try
		{
			String[] parts = command.split(" ");    //Split the command into parts
			PrintWriter pw = new PrintWriter(new FileWriter("npcList.txt", true));  //Create a new PrintWriter object (change npclist.txt
			String name = parts[1];
			String ID = parts[2];
			String cordX = parts[3];
			String cordY = parts[4];     
			pw.println(name + " " + ID + " " + cordX + " " + cordY);     //Print the information to the npcList.txt
			sendMessage("NPC Sucessfully Mapped");
		} catch(Exception e) {System.out.println(e);}

	}

I don’t have WhiteScape, so I don’t know how it works, but you could probably tweak that to work with it.

EDIT: Ok, im sorry. WhiteScape is nothing like I thought it was. I’ll work on the code some more. Sorry 'bout that.
